      "type": "General Statements: All Other Content",
      "notes": "Vitamin B-12 is an essential nutrient that cannot be produced by animals or plants, only by microorganisms. Most of B-12's benefits are related to its coenzyme activity, such as enzymes needed for the production of DNA during cell division.  It is also necessary for the methylation of homocysteine, a harmful by-product of protein metabolism. Folic Acid is included as a synergist and is also necessary for the safe conversion of homocysteine to L-cysteine.*"
